headline.main: NAZI-SOVIET MOVES VIEWED AS 'DICKER'; Both Nations Held Jockeying for New Parley on Price of Moscow's Cooperation EARLY CLASH IS DOUBTED Bluff and Counter-Bluff Seen in Russia's Waiting Game for Share in Spoils

lead_paragraph: TOKYO, May 1 -- The attitude and behavior of Soviet Russia during the last two months seems to have created the impression in the United States and Great Britain that events are working up to a showdown between Russia and Germany. This strikes your correspondent as one more instance of wishful thinking.
abstract: German-USSR rift doubted; dicker on USSR cooperation price reptd
